The paper discusses the use of deep learning architectures for natural language processing tasks in the medical domain, specifically for filtering and re-ranking answers in question answering. This falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of pre-trained models and multi-task learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the use of language inference and question entailment techniques may suggest a focus on cognitive science (cs.CY).
